        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/2bfe46/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-07-29T16:48:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"284493\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>The first vintage of my ongoing vertical but I take it there will not be so many more.  You aren\u2019t going to believe me when I say this drinks like a village gevrey from a top producer, but it\u2019s true.  It\u2019s a miracle of a wine.  It\u2019s a deep garnet color right now with a nose of licorice and cherry and sous bois.  It\u2019s completely integrated in the mouth and lingers for a while. While it\u2019s not astonishing that someone can make burgundy like this, it is astonishing that it can cost so little and that the label can read \u201ccote de nuits village\u201d.  I\u2019m tempted to say that we should ask more of others but I\u2019ve been at this long enough to know that these wines are just special.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I will soon open the Fornerol Rouge Rouge C\u00f4tes de Nuits Villages rue des foins 2018.</p>\n<p>My last tasting was a real success :<br>\nFornerol Rouge Rouge C\u00f4tes de Nuits Villages 2017 : 16,5/20 \u2013 7/6/2022</p>\n<p>The CDNV 2001 was stunning in 2018.</p>",
